      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Sunday. ¶  ¶ I am sending you, dear friend, a just arrived reprint of the journal of Forrest's last journey, ¶ Presumably J. Forrest (1875a). ¶  ¶ thinking that it will interest you. But will you be s...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">75.00.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Julius von Haast</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">MS papers 37, no 622, folder 213, Haast family papers, Alexander Turnbull Library, Wellington.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS is undated; the reference to Haast's wife indicates that it was written after mid-April 1875 (see n. 4).</p>
               </note>Sonntag.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich sende Ihnen, bester Freund, einen eben angekommenen Abdruck des Journals<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>von Forrest's letzter Reise, denkend dass selbiges Sie interessiren wird. Wollen Sie es mir freundlich vor dem Abgang der Post (nach Europa) zurück senden, da ich diesen Druck an Petermann senden möchte, und nur das eine Exemplar erhielt.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lassen Sie mich hoffen dass Ihre Gemahlin nun ganz erstarken wird u sich in Ihrer Umgebung auch wieder geistig ermannet.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sunday.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sending you, dear friend, a just arrived reprint of the journal of Forrest's last journey,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presumably J. Forrest (1875a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>thinking that it will interest you. But will you be so kind as to return it to me before the next mail (to Europe), as I should like to send this publication to Petermann,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is no mention in the surviving correspondence of M's sending such a publication to Petermann.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and only received the one copy.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope that your wife will now get her strength back completely and in your own surroundings will also be able to pull herself together mentally.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mary Haast had a severe nervous breakdown following the birth of her fourth son, Julius Hermann, in December 1873<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(H. F. von Haast (1948), p. 682),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in October 1874<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>went<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to stay with her parents in Victoria, where her father, Edward Dobson, was engineer for the construction of the Geelong Waterworks. Julius Haast arrived in Melbourne aboard<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Albion</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on 26 February 1875 to join his wife (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 27 February 1875, p. 6) and he and Mary returned to New Zealand on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Tararua</seg>, which cleared out of Melbourne on 6 April 1875 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 10 April 1875, p. 14) and arrived at Lyttelton on 15 April 1875 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Globe</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Christchurch), 15 April 1875, p. 2).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
